      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "SHOWMETHETANLINES NZ (3) drew much wider and worked when parked so was far from disgraced when midfield in the Simpson Memorial last start. Was racing well prior and owns a 50 per cent strike rate at this circuit and distance. Should get every chance from a much better draw. SOHO TRUMP (8) beat Showmethetanlines home when a resuming third in the Simpson Memorial then led from a low draw and was too good last start, giving him two wins and a placing from three attempts at this circuit and distance. Tougher from this draw but he is a talent. REWATCH (6) came from wider for a resuming win here. This is stronger but he'll be fitter and looks to have returned in good order. EYENEEDTHAT (1) progressed off a midfield effort at Listed level when resuming to finish runner-up in Victoria last start. Building in fitness and is aided by the ace draw.",
